Package: RMTnet
Title: Random Matrix Theory for Gene Co-Expression Networks
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Felix", "Borrego", email = "felix.borrego02@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Constructs gene co-expression networks using Random Matrix Theory
    (RMT) to distinguish statistically significant correlations from finite-sample
    noise. Provides a parameter-free alternative to WGCNA's soft thresholding by
    applying the Marchenko-Pastur law to determine a mathematically principled
    noise threshold. Includes spectral filtering of correlation matrices, gene
    module detection, and diagnostic visualizations.
